attributes.dcp_projectname: Shubert - Cort Theatre Rehab Special Permit
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: Special Permit pursuant to Section 81-745 (theater rehabilitation bonus) for 119,293 sf of bonus floor area. Also, text amendment to Section 81-745 to allow bonus floor area obtained through special permit to be utilized without regard to underlying zoning district boundaries.

An application by the New York City Department of Transportation involving the change of legal grade of Grand Concourse in order to facilitate the rehabilitation of the Grand Concourse bridge over Metro North Railroad in Community District 6, Borough of The Bronx.

This is a private application by Calvanico Associates requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate a new building at 40 Yeomalt Avenue in Huguenot neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by 18-17 130th Street LLC requesting a special permit to facilitate expansion of an existing one-story building to allow a second floor for accessory office use at 18-17 130th Street, College Point, Community District 7, Queens.

This is a private application by 1114 6th Avenue Owner LLC for two certifications pursuant to Section 37-625 (Design Changes) and Section 37-73 (Certification) to facilitate changes to an existing Privately Owned Public Space at 1114 Sixth Avenue (aka Grace Plaza) in the Midtown neighborhood of Manhattan, Community District 5.

attributes.dcp_projectname: Spring Creek Park Addition - Site Selection / Acq
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a public application by DPR requesting a Combination Site Selection/Acquisition (PC) of four vacant and unimproved privately-owned sites and a mapped but unbuilt portion of Drew Street for assignment to NYC Parks to facilitate the ecological restoration of Spring Creek Park by DPR, in partnership with the Army Corps of Engineers, at CD 5,  East New York, Brooklyn.
attributes.actiontypes: Combination Acquisition and Site Selection by the

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: UDAAP/disposition for city-owned property at West 22nd St and 7th Avenue for the redevelopment of a mixed-use commercial and residential development

This is a private application by Eric Evans requesting authorizations ZR 105-421, 105-422 and 105-431 to facilitate construction of a new accessory in-ground swimming pool, patio and cabana area at 119 Nevada Avenue in Todt Hill neighborhood, Community District 2, Staten Island.

Zoning map amendment from R2 to R2X to facilitate development and enlargement of single-family homes in the Kew Gardens Hills neighborhood in Queens Community District 8.   A zoning text amendment to ZR Section 21-12 is required to enable this rezoning.  No additional dwelling units are proposed or anticipated to result from this zoning map amendment.
Rezoning of 3 blocks from M2-1/M1-4 to M2-4.
This is a private application requesting a rezoning from M1-1D to R8A/C2-4 to facilitate redevelopment at 737 Fourth Avenue in Greenwood Heights, Community District 7, Brooklyn.

This is a public application by HPD requesting a UDAAP Designation, project approval and approval of disposition of city-owned land to facilitate the development of three sites in Community District 5, Brooklyn.

This is a City application by NYC DOT, DEP, SBS, and DCAS for the acquisition of real property and a text amendment to Section 62-59(c) to facilitate the development of the East Side Coastal Resiliency (ESCR) project. ESCR is a comprehensive flood protection system that reduces flood risk, improves access to the waterfront, and enhances waterfront parkland along the East River from Montgomery Street to East 25th Street in Manhattan Community Districts 3 and 6.
attributes.actiontypes: Acquisition of Property by the City;Zoning Text

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Halcyon Management Group requesting a phased implementation certification pursuant to ZR 62-811 and substantial compliance of the previously approved waterfront certification (N 150371ZCK) to facilitate a mixed-use development at 27-41 West Street, Greenpoint, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

This is a private application by Philip Rampulla requesting certification ZR 119-04 to facilitate a new building at 1 Sunset Hill Drive in the Silver Lake neighborhood, Community Board #1, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Mike Siad requesting certification to alter an existing one family and construct a new single family home at 25 Callan Avenue in Todt Hill, Comunity Board #2, Staten Island.

attributes.dcp_projectname: New York City Borough - Based Jail System
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: New York City Mayor's Office of Criminal Justice and Department of Corrections are proposing to implement a borough-based jail system as part of the City’s continued commitment to create a modern, humane and safe justice system. The proposed project would develop four new detention facilities to house individuals who are in the City’s correctional custody with one located in each of the Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, and Queens. MIH is proposed to be mapped on western portion of the Bronx site.
attributes.actiontypes: Site Selection (City Facility);Zoning Special Permit;Zoning Map Amendment;Zoning Text Amendment;Change in City Map;Urban Development Action Area - UDAAP;Acquisition of Property by the City

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Fleet Center, Inc. for a zoning map amendment from R6 to C6-4 and zoning text amendment to expand the Special Downtown Brooklyn district and create a new MIH area to facilitate a new 205,000 square foot commercial office building at 101 Fleet Place in the Downtown Brooklyn area of Brooklyn Community District 2.

This is a private application by Olnick Organization, Inc. requesting a zoning map amendment and several actions to waive bulk and parking requirements and a zoning text amendment to establish a Mandatory Inclusionary Housing (MIH). The proposed actions would facilitate infill construction of five new mixed-use buildings with approximately 1,600 residential units in Manhattan Community Board 10.
attributes.actiontypes: Zoning Special Permit;Zoning Authorization;Zoning Map;Zoning Special;Zoning Text

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Tony Sayad requesting a certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate new buildings on Bartow Street in Great Kills neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.  Subdivision of one zoning lot into four zoning lots.

This is a private application by ArchCare requesting (1) a zoning map change and (2) the mapping of a Mandatory Inclusionary Housing (MIH) area on the site to facilitate the construction of a new 33-story residential building, a new supportive housing building, a new medical facility, and the consolidation of Terence Cardinal Cooke's operations into a renovated and modernized building.

attributes.dcp_projectname: THE LESBIAN, GAY, BISEXUAL, TRANSGENDER COMMUNITY

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by 111 Petrus Avenue LLC requesting certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate a new building at 111 Petrus Avenue in Eltingville neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Alan Becker requesting certifications ZR 107-08 & 107-121 to facilitate subdivision of one zoning lot into three zoning lots at 35 Madsen Avenue in Richmond Valley neighborhood, Community District 3, Staten Island.

This is a public application by HPD and Phipps Houses as a co-applicants, requesting a zoning map change from R7-2 to C6-2, zoning text amendment to Appendix F to establish an MIH Area, a Zoning Special Permit (74-681), a disposition of City-owned property to facilitate a new 10-story, 100% affordable residential development, including 1,115 of community facility space and approximately 55 dwelling units, proposed for location at 156 Brook Avenue in Mott Haven in Bronx CD 1.
attributes.actiontypes: Disposition of Urban Renewal;Urban Development Action Area -;Zoning Map;Zoning Text;Zoning Special

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: Proposal to provide C1-3 Comercial Overlay on existing legal but non-conforming lot to bring into conformance in Whitestone, Queens.

This is a private application by Alfred Quinones requesting a zoning map amendment to facilitate a new 4-story plus cellar mixed use building with approx. 37,278 s.f. of residential floor area and approx. 6,203 s.f. of ground floor commercial space in the Castle Hill section of Bronx CD 9.

This is a private application by William Petrouleous requesting  ZR 105-421 authorization and ZR 105-90 certification to facilitate zoning lot subdivision and development of new single-family house on one newly created zoning lot, at 120 Whitlock Avenue in the Todt Hill neighborhood, Community District 2, Staten Island.

This is a private application requesting a zoning map amendment to create a new C2-4 overlay over Block 7280 in Brighton Beach Brooklyn. This action would facilitate the development of a new mixed use building.

A series of land use actions, including Zoning Map and Zoning Text Amendments, disposition of city-owned property, and UDAAP approval, to facilitate the Bay Street Corridor Neighborhood Plan. The Plan is intended to connect the existing mixed-use town centers of St. George, Tompkinsville and Stapleton by fostering a new walkable neighborhood with opportunities for new housing, businesses, and jobs.
attributes.actiontypes: Zoning Text Amendment;Disposition of Non-Residential City-Owned;Zoning Text;Zoning Map;Urban Development Action Area - UDAAP

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is an application by HPD for a disposition of city-owned property to facilitate a 123-unit affordable senior housing in Preservation Area A of the Special Little Italy District, in Nolita, Community District 2, Manhattan.

This is a private application by Tavros Capital Partners requesting a zoning text amendment of Sections 117-421(c)(1) and (2) and Appendix B of Article XI, Chapter 7 of the Zoning Resolution, to facilitate the development of a 45-story mixed-use building, at 23-10 45th Avenue in the Court Square neighborhood of Long Island City, Community District 2, Queens.

This is a private application by 419 MM LLC requesting a special permit pursuant to ZR Section 74-711 to allow Use Group 6 retail and office uses below the level of the second story and height and setback waivers to facilitate the development of an 8-story commercial building and the restoration of a historic row-house, at 419 Broadway in SoHo, Community District 2, Manhattan.

This is a private application by Carmine Deross requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate new buildings at 718 Bloomingdale Road in Rossville neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.  Requesting subdivision of one zoning lot into 12 zoning lots with school seat certification for 12 dwelling units.
A private application to rezone an R5B ro R5B/C1-3 to facilitate the legalization of an existing office use.

This is a private application by Anthony Franco requesting a certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate a new building at 446 & 450 Vineland Avenue in Annadale neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Jeff Barratta requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate new building development at 66 Oswald Place in Prince's Bay, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

Special permit pursuant to Sections 37-622 and 74-761 to reduce plaza area, and Authorization pursuant to Sections 37-623 and 37-727 to permit a nighttime closure of certain portions of a bonused plaza. Application MAY include one or more open air cafés and a kiosk pursuant to Section 37-73.

This is a private application by LERA Property Holdings, LLC requesting authorizations pursuant to ZR 105-421 and 105-425 to facilitate three (3) one-family homes developed at 405 St. George Road in Lighthouse Hill, Community Board #2, Staten Island.

attributes.dcp_projectname: Shubert - Cort Theatre Rehab Special Permit
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: Special Permit pursuant to Section 81-745 (theater rehabilitation bonus) for 119,293 sf of bonus floor area. Also, text amendment to Section 81-745 to allow bonus floor area obtained through special permit to be utilized without regard to underlying zoning district boundaries.

An application by the New York City Department of Transportation involving the change of legal grade of Grand Concourse in order to facilitate the rehabilitation of the Grand Concourse bridge over Metro North Railroad in Community District 6, Borough of The Bronx.

This is a private application by Calvanico Associates requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate a new building at 40 Yeomalt Avenue in Huguenot neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by 18-17 130th Street LLC requesting a special permit to facilitate expansion of an existing one-story building to allow a second floor for accessory office use at 18-17 130th Street, College Point, Community District 7, Queens.

This is a private application by 1114 6th Avenue Owner LLC for two certifications pursuant to Section 37-625 (Design Changes) and Section 37-73 (Certification) to facilitate changes to an existing Privately Owned Public Space at 1114 Sixth Avenue (aka Grace Plaza) in the Midtown neighborhood of Manhattan, Community District 5.

attributes.dcp_projectname: Spring Creek Park Addition - Site Selection / Acq
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a public application by DPR requesting a Combination Site Selection/Acquisition (PC) of four vacant and unimproved privately-owned sites and a mapped but unbuilt portion of Drew Street for assignment to NYC Parks to facilitate the ecological restoration of Spring Creek Park by DPR, in partnership with the Army Corps of Engineers, at CD 5,  East New York, Brooklyn.
attributes.actiontypes: Combination Acquisition and Site Selection by the

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: UDAAP/disposition for city-owned property at West 22nd St and 7th Avenue for the redevelopment of a mixed-use commercial and residential development

This is a private application by Eric Evans requesting authorizations ZR 105-421, 105-422 and 105-431 to facilitate construction of a new accessory in-ground swimming pool, patio and cabana area at 119 Nevada Avenue in Todt Hill neighborhood, Community District 2, Staten Island.

Zoning map amendment from R2 to R2X to facilitate development and enlargement of single-family homes in the Kew Gardens Hills neighborhood in Queens Community District 8.   A zoning text amendment to ZR Section 21-12 is required to enable this rezoning.  No additional dwelling units are proposed or anticipated to result from this zoning map amendment.
Rezoning of 3 blocks from M2-1/M1-4 to M2-4.
This is a private application requesting a rezoning from M1-1D to R8A/C2-4 to facilitate redevelopment at 737 Fourth Avenue in Greenwood Heights, Community District 7, Brooklyn.

This is a public application by HPD requesting a UDAAP Designation, project approval and approval of disposition of city-owned land to facilitate the development of three sites in Community District 5, Brooklyn.

This is a City application by NYC DOT, DEP, SBS, and DCAS for the acquisition of real property and a text amendment to Section 62-59(c) to facilitate the development of the East Side Coastal Resiliency (ESCR) project. ESCR is a comprehensive flood protection system that reduces flood risk, improves access to the waterfront, and enhances waterfront parkland along the East River from Montgomery Street to East 25th Street in Manhattan Community Districts 3 and 6.
attributes.actiontypes: Acquisition of Property by the City;Zoning Text

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Halcyon Management Group requesting a phased implementation certification pursuant to ZR 62-811 and substantial compliance of the previously approved waterfront certification (N 150371ZCK) to facilitate a mixed-use development at 27-41 West Street, Greenpoint, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

This is a private application by Philip Rampulla requesting certification ZR 119-04 to facilitate a new building at 1 Sunset Hill Drive in the Silver Lake neighborhood, Community Board #1, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Mike Siad requesting certification to alter an existing one family and construct a new single family home at 25 Callan Avenue in Todt Hill, Comunity Board #2, Staten Island.

attributes.dcp_projectname: New York City Borough - Based Jail System
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: New York City Mayor's Office of Criminal Justice and Department of Corrections are proposing to implement a borough-based jail system as part of the City’s continued commitment to create a modern, humane and safe justice system. The proposed project would develop four new detention facilities to house individuals who are in the City’s correctional custody with one located in each of the Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, and Queens. MIH is proposed to be mapped on western portion of the Bronx site.
attributes.actiontypes: Site Selection (City Facility);Zoning Special Permit;Zoning Map Amendment;Zoning Text Amendment;Change in City Map;Urban Development Action Area - UDAAP;Acquisition of Property by the City

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Fleet Center, Inc. for a zoning map amendment from R6 to C6-4 and zoning text amendment to expand the Special Downtown Brooklyn district and create a new MIH area to facilitate a new 205,000 square foot commercial office building at 101 Fleet Place in the Downtown Brooklyn area of Brooklyn Community District 2.

This is a private application by Olnick Organization, Inc. requesting a zoning map amendment and several actions to waive bulk and parking requirements and a zoning text amendment to establish a Mandatory Inclusionary Housing (MIH). The proposed actions would facilitate infill construction of five new mixed-use buildings with approximately 1,600 residential units in Manhattan Community Board 10.
attributes.actiontypes: Zoning Special Permit;Zoning Authorization;Zoning Map;Zoning Special;Zoning Text

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Tony Sayad requesting a certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate new buildings on Bartow Street in Great Kills neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.  Subdivision of one zoning lot into four zoning lots.

This is a private application by ArchCare requesting (1) a zoning map change and (2) the mapping of a Mandatory Inclusionary Housing (MIH) area on the site to facilitate the construction of a new 33-story residential building, a new supportive housing building, a new medical facility, and the consolidation of Terence Cardinal Cooke's operations into a renovated and modernized building.

attributes.dcp_projectname: THE LESBIAN, GAY, BISEXUAL, TRANSGENDER COMMUNITY

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by 111 Petrus Avenue LLC requesting certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate a new building at 111 Petrus Avenue in Eltingville neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Alan Becker requesting certifications ZR 107-08 & 107-121 to facilitate subdivision of one zoning lot into three zoning lots at 35 Madsen Avenue in Richmond Valley neighborhood, Community District 3, Staten Island.

This is a public application by HPD and Phipps Houses as a co-applicants, requesting a zoning map change from R7-2 to C6-2, zoning text amendment to Appendix F to establish an MIH Area, a Zoning Special Permit (74-681), a disposition of City-owned property to facilitate a new 10-story, 100% affordable residential development, including 1,115 of community facility space and approximately 55 dwelling units, proposed for location at 156 Brook Avenue in Mott Haven in Bronx CD 1.
attributes.actiontypes: Disposition of Urban Renewal;Urban Development Action Area -;Zoning Map;Zoning Text;Zoning Special

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: Proposal to provide C1-3 Comercial Overlay on existing legal but non-conforming lot to bring into conformance in Whitestone, Queens.

This is a private application by Alfred Quinones requesting a zoning map amendment to facilitate a new 4-story plus cellar mixed use building with approx. 37,278 s.f. of residential floor area and approx. 6,203 s.f. of ground floor commercial space in the Castle Hill section of Bronx CD 9.

This is a private application by William Petrouleous requesting  ZR 105-421 authorization and ZR 105-90 certification to facilitate zoning lot subdivision and development of new single-family house on one newly created zoning lot, at 120 Whitlock Avenue in the Todt Hill neighborhood, Community District 2, Staten Island.

This is a private application requesting a zoning map amendment to create a new C2-4 overlay over Block 7280 in Brighton Beach Brooklyn. This action would facilitate the development of a new mixed use building.

A series of land use actions, including Zoning Map and Zoning Text Amendments, disposition of city-owned property, and UDAAP approval, to facilitate the Bay Street Corridor Neighborhood Plan. The Plan is intended to connect the existing mixed-use town centers of St. George, Tompkinsville and Stapleton by fostering a new walkable neighborhood with opportunities for new housing, businesses, and jobs.
attributes.actiontypes: Zoning Text Amendment;Disposition of Non-Residential City-Owned;Zoning Text;Zoning Map;Urban Development Action Area - UDAAP

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is an application by HPD for a disposition of city-owned property to facilitate a 123-unit affordable senior housing in Preservation Area A of the Special Little Italy District, in Nolita, Community District 2, Manhattan.

This is a private application by Tavros Capital Partners requesting a zoning text amendment of Sections 117-421(c)(1) and (2) and Appendix B of Article XI, Chapter 7 of the Zoning Resolution, to facilitate the development of a 45-story mixed-use building, at 23-10 45th Avenue in the Court Square neighborhood of Long Island City, Community District 2, Queens.

This is a private application by 419 MM LLC requesting a special permit pursuant to ZR Section 74-711 to allow Use Group 6 retail and office uses below the level of the second story and height and setback waivers to facilitate the development of an 8-story commercial building and the restoration of a historic row-house, at 419 Broadway in SoHo, Community District 2, Manhattan.

This is a private application by Carmine Deross requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate new buildings at 718 Bloomingdale Road in Rossville neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.  Requesting subdivision of one zoning lot into 12 zoning lots with school seat certification for 12 dwelling units.
A private application to rezone an R5B ro R5B/C1-3 to facilitate the legalization of an existing office use.

This is a private application by Anthony Franco requesting a certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate a new building at 446 & 450 Vineland Avenue in Annadale neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Jeff Barratta requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate new building development at 66 Oswald Place in Prince's Bay, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

Special permit pursuant to Sections 37-622 and 74-761 to reduce plaza area, and Authorization pursuant to Sections 37-623 and 37-727 to permit a nighttime closure of certain portions of a bonused plaza. Application MAY include one or more open air cafés and a kiosk pursuant to Section 37-73.

This is a private application by LERA Property Holdings, LLC requesting authorizations pursuant to ZR 105-421 and 105-425 to facilitate three (3) one-family homes developed at 405 St. George Road in Lighthouse Hill, Community Board #2, Staten Island.

attributes.dcp_projectname: Shubert - Cort Theatre Rehab Special Permit
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: Special Permit pursuant to Section 81-745 (theater rehabilitation bonus) for 119,293 sf of bonus floor area. Also, text amendment to Section 81-745 to allow bonus floor area obtained through special permit to be utilized without regard to underlying zoning district boundaries.

An application by the New York City Department of Transportation involving the change of legal grade of Grand Concourse in order to facilitate the rehabilitation of the Grand Concourse bridge over Metro North Railroad in Community District 6, Borough of The Bronx.

This is a private application by Calvanico Associates requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate a new building at 40 Yeomalt Avenue in Huguenot neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by 18-17 130th Street LLC requesting a special permit to facilitate expansion of an existing one-story building to allow a second floor for accessory office use at 18-17 130th Street, College Point, Community District 7, Queens.

This is a private application by 1114 6th Avenue Owner LLC for two certifications pursuant to Section 37-625 (Design Changes) and Section 37-73 (Certification) to facilitate changes to an existing Privately Owned Public Space at 1114 Sixth Avenue (aka Grace Plaza) in the Midtown neighborhood of Manhattan, Community District 5.

attributes.dcp_projectname: Spring Creek Park Addition - Site Selection / Acq
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a public application by DPR requesting a Combination Site Selection/Acquisition (PC) of four vacant and unimproved privately-owned sites and a mapped but unbuilt portion of Drew Street for assignment to NYC Parks to facilitate the ecological restoration of Spring Creek Park by DPR, in partnership with the Army Corps of Engineers, at CD 5,  East New York, Brooklyn.
attributes.actiontypes: Combination Acquisition and Site Selection by the

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: UDAAP/disposition for city-owned property at West 22nd St and 7th Avenue for the redevelopment of a mixed-use commercial and residential development

This is a private application by Eric Evans requesting authorizations ZR 105-421, 105-422 and 105-431 to facilitate construction of a new accessory in-ground swimming pool, patio and cabana area at 119 Nevada Avenue in Todt Hill neighborhood, Community District 2, Staten Island.

Zoning map amendment from R2 to R2X to facilitate development and enlargement of single-family homes in the Kew Gardens Hills neighborhood in Queens Community District 8.   A zoning text amendment to ZR Section 21-12 is required to enable this rezoning.  No additional dwelling units are proposed or anticipated to result from this zoning map amendment.
Rezoning of 3 blocks from M2-1/M1-4 to M2-4.
This is a private application requesting a rezoning from M1-1D to R8A/C2-4 to facilitate redevelopment at 737 Fourth Avenue in Greenwood Heights, Community District 7, Brooklyn.

This is a public application by HPD requesting a UDAAP Designation, project approval and approval of disposition of city-owned land to facilitate the development of three sites in Community District 5, Brooklyn.

This is a City application by NYC DOT, DEP, SBS, and DCAS for the acquisition of real property and a text amendment to Section 62-59(c) to facilitate the development of the East Side Coastal Resiliency (ESCR) project. ESCR is a comprehensive flood protection system that reduces flood risk, improves access to the waterfront, and enhances waterfront parkland along the East River from Montgomery Street to East 25th Street in Manhattan Community Districts 3 and 6.
attributes.actiontypes: Acquisition of Property by the City;Zoning Text

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Halcyon Management Group requesting a phased implementation certification pursuant to ZR 62-811 and substantial compliance of the previously approved waterfront certification (N 150371ZCK) to facilitate a mixed-use development at 27-41 West Street, Greenpoint, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

This is a private application by Philip Rampulla requesting certification ZR 119-04 to facilitate a new building at 1 Sunset Hill Drive in the Silver Lake neighborhood, Community Board #1, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Mike Siad requesting certification to alter an existing one family and construct a new single family home at 25 Callan Avenue in Todt Hill, Comunity Board #2, Staten Island.

attributes.dcp_projectname: New York City Borough - Based Jail System
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: New York City Mayor's Office of Criminal Justice and Department of Corrections are proposing to implement a borough-based jail system as part of the City’s continued commitment to create a modern, humane and safe justice system. The proposed project would develop four new detention facilities to house individuals who are in the City’s correctional custody with one located in each of the Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, and Queens. MIH is proposed to be mapped on western portion of the Bronx site.
attributes.actiontypes: Site Selection (City Facility);Zoning Special Permit;Zoning Map Amendment;Zoning Text Amendment;Change in City Map;Urban Development Action Area - UDAAP;Acquisition of Property by the City

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Fleet Center, Inc. for a zoning map amendment from R6 to C6-4 and zoning text amendment to expand the Special Downtown Brooklyn district and create a new MIH area to facilitate a new 205,000 square foot commercial office building at 101 Fleet Place in the Downtown Brooklyn area of Brooklyn Community District 2.

This is a private application by Olnick Organization, Inc. requesting a zoning map amendment and several actions to waive bulk and parking requirements and a zoning text amendment to establish a Mandatory Inclusionary Housing (MIH). The proposed actions would facilitate infill construction of five new mixed-use buildings with approximately 1,600 residential units in Manhattan Community Board 10.
attributes.actiontypes: Zoning Special Permit;Zoning Authorization;Zoning Map;Zoning Special;Zoning Text

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Tony Sayad requesting a certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate new buildings on Bartow Street in Great Kills neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.  Subdivision of one zoning lot into four zoning lots.

This is a private application by ArchCare requesting (1) a zoning map change and (2) the mapping of a Mandatory Inclusionary Housing (MIH) area on the site to facilitate the construction of a new 33-story residential building, a new supportive housing building, a new medical facility, and the consolidation of Terence Cardinal Cooke's operations into a renovated and modernized building.

attributes.dcp_projectname: THE LESBIAN, GAY, BISEXUAL, TRANSGENDER COMMUNITY

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by 111 Petrus Avenue LLC requesting certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate a new building at 111 Petrus Avenue in Eltingville neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Alan Becker requesting certifications ZR 107-08 & 107-121 to facilitate subdivision of one zoning lot into three zoning lots at 35 Madsen Avenue in Richmond Valley neighborhood, Community District 3, Staten Island.

This is a public application by HPD and Phipps Houses as a co-applicants, requesting a zoning map change from R7-2 to C6-2, zoning text amendment to Appendix F to establish an MIH Area, a Zoning Special Permit (74-681), a disposition of City-owned property to facilitate a new 10-story, 100% affordable residential development, including 1,115 of community facility space and approximately 55 dwelling units, proposed for location at 156 Brook Avenue in Mott Haven in Bronx CD 1.
attributes.actiontypes: Disposition of Urban Renewal;Urban Development Action Area -;Zoning Map;Zoning Text;Zoning Special

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: Proposal to provide C1-3 Comercial Overlay on existing legal but non-conforming lot to bring into conformance in Whitestone, Queens.

This is a private application by Alfred Quinones requesting a zoning map amendment to facilitate a new 4-story plus cellar mixed use building with approx. 37,278 s.f. of residential floor area and approx. 6,203 s.f. of ground floor commercial space in the Castle Hill section of Bronx CD 9.

This is a private application by William Petrouleous requesting  ZR 105-421 authorization and ZR 105-90 certification to facilitate zoning lot subdivision and development of new single-family house on one newly created zoning lot, at 120 Whitlock Avenue in the Todt Hill neighborhood, Community District 2, Staten Island.

This is a private application requesting a zoning map amendment to create a new C2-4 overlay over Block 7280 in Brighton Beach Brooklyn. This action would facilitate the development of a new mixed use building.

A series of land use actions, including Zoning Map and Zoning Text Amendments, disposition of city-owned property, and UDAAP approval, to facilitate the Bay Street Corridor Neighborhood Plan. The Plan is intended to connect the existing mixed-use town centers of St. George, Tompkinsville and Stapleton by fostering a new walkable neighborhood with opportunities for new housing, businesses, and jobs.
attributes.actiontypes: Zoning Text Amendment;Disposition of Non-Residential City-Owned;Zoning Text;Zoning Map;Urban Development Action Area - UDAAP

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is an application by HPD for a disposition of city-owned property to facilitate a 123-unit affordable senior housing in Preservation Area A of the Special Little Italy District, in Nolita, Community District 2, Manhattan.

This is a private application by Tavros Capital Partners requesting a zoning text amendment of Sections 117-421(c)(1) and (2) and Appendix B of Article XI, Chapter 7 of the Zoning Resolution, to facilitate the development of a 45-story mixed-use building, at 23-10 45th Avenue in the Court Square neighborhood of Long Island City, Community District 2, Queens.

This is a private application by 419 MM LLC requesting a special permit pursuant to ZR Section 74-711 to allow Use Group 6 retail and office uses below the level of the second story and height and setback waivers to facilitate the development of an 8-story commercial building and the restoration of a historic row-house, at 419 Broadway in SoHo, Community District 2, Manhattan.

This is a private application by Carmine Deross requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate new buildings at 718 Bloomingdale Road in Rossville neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.  Requesting subdivision of one zoning lot into 12 zoning lots with school seat certification for 12 dwelling units.
A private application to rezone an R5B ro R5B/C1-3 to facilitate the legalization of an existing office use.

This is a private application by Anthony Franco requesting a certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate a new building at 446 & 450 Vineland Avenue in Annadale neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Jeff Barratta requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate new building development at 66 Oswald Place in Prince's Bay, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

Special permit pursuant to Sections 37-622 and 74-761 to reduce plaza area, and Authorization pursuant to Sections 37-623 and 37-727 to permit a nighttime closure of certain portions of a bonused plaza. Application MAY include one or more open air cafés and a kiosk pursuant to Section 37-73.

This is a private application by LERA Property Holdings, LLC requesting authorizations pursuant to ZR 105-421 and 105-425 to facilitate three (3) one-family homes developed at 405 St. George Road in Lighthouse Hill, Community Board #2, Staten Island.

attributes.dcp_projectname: Shubert - Cort Theatre Rehab Special Permit
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: Special Permit pursuant to Section 81-745 (theater rehabilitation bonus) for 119,293 sf of bonus floor area. Also, text amendment to Section 81-745 to allow bonus floor area obtained through special permit to be utilized without regard to underlying zoning district boundaries.

An application by the New York City Department of Transportation involving the change of legal grade of Grand Concourse in order to facilitate the rehabilitation of the Grand Concourse bridge over Metro North Railroad in Community District 6, Borough of The Bronx.

This is a private application by Calvanico Associates requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate a new building at 40 Yeomalt Avenue in Huguenot neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by 18-17 130th Street LLC requesting a special permit to facilitate expansion of an existing one-story building to allow a second floor for accessory office use at 18-17 130th Street, College Point, Community District 7, Queens.

This is a private application by 1114 6th Avenue Owner LLC for two certifications pursuant to Section 37-625 (Design Changes) and Section 37-73 (Certification) to facilitate changes to an existing Privately Owned Public Space at 1114 Sixth Avenue (aka Grace Plaza) in the Midtown neighborhood of Manhattan, Community District 5.

attributes.dcp_projectname: Spring Creek Park Addition - Site Selection / Acq
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a public application by DPR requesting a Combination Site Selection/Acquisition (PC) of four vacant and unimproved privately-owned sites and a mapped but unbuilt portion of Drew Street for assignment to NYC Parks to facilitate the ecological restoration of Spring Creek Park by DPR, in partnership with the Army Corps of Engineers, at CD 5,  East New York, Brooklyn.
attributes.actiontypes: Combination Acquisition and Site Selection by the

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: UDAAP/disposition for city-owned property at West 22nd St and 7th Avenue for the redevelopment of a mixed-use commercial and residential development

This is a private application by Eric Evans requesting authorizations ZR 105-421, 105-422 and 105-431 to facilitate construction of a new accessory in-ground swimming pool, patio and cabana area at 119 Nevada Avenue in Todt Hill neighborhood, Community District 2, Staten Island.

Zoning map amendment from R2 to R2X to facilitate development and enlargement of single-family homes in the Kew Gardens Hills neighborhood in Queens Community District 8.   A zoning text amendment to ZR Section 21-12 is required to enable this rezoning.  No additional dwelling units are proposed or anticipated to result from this zoning map amendment.
Rezoning of 3 blocks from M2-1/M1-4 to M2-4.
This is a private application requesting a rezoning from M1-1D to R8A/C2-4 to facilitate redevelopment at 737 Fourth Avenue in Greenwood Heights, Community District 7, Brooklyn.

This is a public application by HPD requesting a UDAAP Designation, project approval and approval of disposition of city-owned land to facilitate the development of three sites in Community District 5, Brooklyn.

This is a City application by NYC DOT, DEP, SBS, and DCAS for the acquisition of real property and a text amendment to Section 62-59(c) to facilitate the development of the East Side Coastal Resiliency (ESCR) project. ESCR is a comprehensive flood protection system that reduces flood risk, improves access to the waterfront, and enhances waterfront parkland along the East River from Montgomery Street to East 25th Street in Manhattan Community Districts 3 and 6.
attributes.actiontypes: Acquisition of Property by the City;Zoning Text

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Halcyon Management Group requesting a phased implementation certification pursuant to ZR 62-811 and substantial compliance of the previously approved waterfront certification (N 150371ZCK) to facilitate a mixed-use development at 27-41 West Street, Greenpoint, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

This is a private application by Philip Rampulla requesting certification ZR 119-04 to facilitate a new building at 1 Sunset Hill Drive in the Silver Lake neighborhood, Community Board #1, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Mike Siad requesting certification to alter an existing one family and construct a new single family home at 25 Callan Avenue in Todt Hill, Comunity Board #2, Staten Island.

attributes.dcp_projectname: New York City Borough - Based Jail System
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: New York City Mayor's Office of Criminal Justice and Department of Corrections are proposing to implement a borough-based jail system as part of the City’s continued commitment to create a modern, humane and safe justice system. The proposed project would develop four new detention facilities to house individuals who are in the City’s correctional custody with one located in each of the Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, and Queens. MIH is proposed to be mapped on western portion of the Bronx site.
attributes.actiontypes: Site Selection (City Facility);Zoning Special Permit;Zoning Map Amendment;Zoning Text Amendment;Change in City Map;Urban Development Action Area - UDAAP;Acquisition of Property by the City

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Fleet Center, Inc. for a zoning map amendment from R6 to C6-4 and zoning text amendment to expand the Special Downtown Brooklyn district and create a new MIH area to facilitate a new 205,000 square foot commercial office building at 101 Fleet Place in the Downtown Brooklyn area of Brooklyn Community District 2.

This is a private application by Olnick Organization, Inc. requesting a zoning map amendment and several actions to waive bulk and parking requirements and a zoning text amendment to establish a Mandatory Inclusionary Housing (MIH). The proposed actions would facilitate infill construction of five new mixed-use buildings with approximately 1,600 residential units in Manhattan Community Board 10.
attributes.actiontypes: Zoning Special Permit;Zoning Authorization;Zoning Map;Zoning Special;Zoning Text

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Tony Sayad requesting a certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate new buildings on Bartow Street in Great Kills neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.  Subdivision of one zoning lot into four zoning lots.

This is a private application by ArchCare requesting (1) a zoning map change and (2) the mapping of a Mandatory Inclusionary Housing (MIH) area on the site to facilitate the construction of a new 33-story residential building, a new supportive housing building, a new medical facility, and the consolidation of Terence Cardinal Cooke's operations into a renovated and modernized building.

attributes.dcp_projectname: THE LESBIAN, GAY, BISEXUAL, TRANSGENDER COMMUNITY

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by 111 Petrus Avenue LLC requesting certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate a new building at 111 Petrus Avenue in Eltingville neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Alan Becker requesting certifications ZR 107-08 & 107-121 to facilitate subdivision of one zoning lot into three zoning lots at 35 Madsen Avenue in Richmond Valley neighborhood, Community District 3, Staten Island.

This is a public application by HPD and Phipps Houses as a co-applicants, requesting a zoning map change from R7-2 to C6-2, zoning text amendment to Appendix F to establish an MIH Area, a Zoning Special Permit (74-681), a disposition of City-owned property to facilitate a new 10-story, 100% affordable residential development, including 1,115 of community facility space and approximately 55 dwelling units, proposed for location at 156 Brook Avenue in Mott Haven in Bronx CD 1.
attributes.actiontypes: Disposition of Urban Renewal;Urban Development Action Area -;Zoning Map;Zoning Text;Zoning Special

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: Proposal to provide C1-3 Comercial Overlay on existing legal but non-conforming lot to bring into conformance in Whitestone, Queens.

This is a private application by Alfred Quinones requesting a zoning map amendment to facilitate a new 4-story plus cellar mixed use building with approx. 37,278 s.f. of residential floor area and approx. 6,203 s.f. of ground floor commercial space in the Castle Hill section of Bronx CD 9.

This is a private application by William Petrouleous requesting  ZR 105-421 authorization and ZR 105-90 certification to facilitate zoning lot subdivision and development of new single-family house on one newly created zoning lot, at 120 Whitlock Avenue in the Todt Hill neighborhood, Community District 2, Staten Island.

This is a private application requesting a zoning map amendment to create a new C2-4 overlay over Block 7280 in Brighton Beach Brooklyn. This action would facilitate the development of a new mixed use building.

A series of land use actions, including Zoning Map and Zoning Text Amendments, disposition of city-owned property, and UDAAP approval, to facilitate the Bay Street Corridor Neighborhood Plan. The Plan is intended to connect the existing mixed-use town centers of St. George, Tompkinsville and Stapleton by fostering a new walkable neighborhood with opportunities for new housing, businesses, and jobs.
attributes.actiontypes: Zoning Text Amendment;Disposition of Non-Residential City-Owned;Zoning Text;Zoning Map;Urban Development Action Area - UDAAP

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is an application by HPD for a disposition of city-owned property to facilitate a 123-unit affordable senior housing in Preservation Area A of the Special Little Italy District, in Nolita, Community District 2, Manhattan.

This is a private application by Tavros Capital Partners requesting a zoning text amendment of Sections 117-421(c)(1) and (2) and Appendix B of Article XI, Chapter 7 of the Zoning Resolution, to facilitate the development of a 45-story mixed-use building, at 23-10 45th Avenue in the Court Square neighborhood of Long Island City, Community District 2, Queens.

This is a private application by 419 MM LLC requesting a special permit pursuant to ZR Section 74-711 to allow Use Group 6 retail and office uses below the level of the second story and height and setback waivers to facilitate the development of an 8-story commercial building and the restoration of a historic row-house, at 419 Broadway in SoHo, Community District 2, Manhattan.

This is a private application by Carmine Deross requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate new buildings at 718 Bloomingdale Road in Rossville neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.  Requesting subdivision of one zoning lot into 12 zoning lots with school seat certification for 12 dwelling units.
A private application to rezone an R5B ro R5B/C1-3 to facilitate the legalization of an existing office use.

This is a private application by Anthony Franco requesting a certification ZR 107-08 to facilitate a new building at 446 & 450 Vineland Avenue in Annadale neighborhood, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

This is a private application by Jeff Barratta requesting certifications ZR 107-08 and 107-121 to facilitate new building development at 66 Oswald Place in Prince's Bay, Community Board #3, Staten Island.

Special permit pursuant to Sections 37-622 and 74-761 to reduce plaza area, and Authorization pursuant to Sections 37-623 and 37-727 to permit a nighttime closure of certain portions of a bonused plaza. Application MAY include one or more open air cafés and a kiosk pursuant to Section 37-73.

This is a private application by LERA Property Holdings, LLC requesting authorizations pursuant to ZR 105-421 and 105-425 to facilitate three (3) one-family homes developed at 405 St. George Road in Lighthouse Hill, Community Board #2, Staten Island.
